.TH "git alias.finishfrom(1) User manual" "" "May, 2020" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
git finishfrom
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git finishfrom branch - rebase from first argument, fast forward merge,
then delete first argument
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git finishfrom is a helper alias to rebase another branch onto HEAD and
then delete that branch.
.IP "1." 3
Ensures that the current HEAD is not a detached HEAD
.IP "2." 3
Ensures that the proper number of arguments have been provided
.IP "3." 3
Ensures that the provided argument is associated with a branch
.IP "4." 3
Calls the rebasefrom alias to rebase the changesets to the source branch
.IP "5." 3
Calls the mergefrom alias to fast-forward merge the HEAD with the source
branch
.IP "6." 3
Deletes the branch since it is not no longer needed
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git finishfrom branch
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
finishto rebasefrom mergefrom
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
finishfrom = \[dq]!f() { : git man finishfrom; \[rs]
    if ! git symbolic-ref HEAD; then echo \[aq]on detached head\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: finishfrom branch\[aq] && return 1; \[rs]
    if ! git show-ref $1; then echo \[aq]branch not a named ref\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    git rebasefrom $1; \[rs]
    git mergefrom $1; \[rs]
    git branch -d $1; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
